Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI)
Work Flow - Information Theoretic Secured InfoSec-(information with need to know)

1. Create new node-domain with optional "universal" this provides cryptographic sovereign isolation from all other sovereign domains.
2. Create Secure Identity -> This becomes SCI-Compartment.
3. Compartment User, creates new device authorisation tokens with ITSDSA512 signatures
4. Individual device used Authorisation token to create a new OS isolated user.
5. Device is registered to SCI-Compartment and universal
6. Access to device is via a mandatory biometric authentication.

Device can store and view SCI information objects with or without "codeword" support.
All communications are asynchronous datagrams and ITS protected via the One Cipher.
